post_text:
A message from NSHS CEO Dr. Wendi Hawk⁣
⁣
The tragic death of George Floyd is a mere glimpse into the systemic racism in our society. We stand with and applaud all citizens legally protesting racism. At NSHS where students are immersed into a college environment, we openly discuss issues such as prejudice, leadership, free speech, and Constitutional rights. We encourage and teach our students to become active in movements that they are passionate about especially when it promotes empowerment. We are proud of our students, alumni, and staff who are taking a stand against racism. We do not condone those who violate the rule of law through random acts of violence because it takes away from the essential message: racism is wrong and cannot be tolerated in any form.⁣
⁣
Be kind to each other. Have a voice, be heard, and stay safe. ⁣
Dr. Wendi Hawk⁣
NSHS CEO

post_text: Governor Sisolak has officially closed Nevada K-12 Schools from March 16 until at least April 6. The State Public Charter School Authority has approved for charter schools to implement an online/virtual curriculum plan for schools who are prepared to implement. NSHS is prepared and is implementing virtual NSHS Study Skills classes as of Monday, 3/16/2020. There is more information available to current students and families on MOODLE.
